name: Aloe
description: Aloe puts liquidity to work by connecting lenders and market-makers. Fully open-source, governance-minimized, and powered by Uniswap.

faq.question: Does aloe charge any fees?
faq.answer: We do not charge any fees to use the protocol. We believe in the power of open-source ecosystems, and provide our interface free-of-charge.  That said, as the protocol earns interest, not all of it goes to you. Some is set aside as "reserves" to help protect against bad debt. This safety mechanism is built into the protocol and operates autonomously.

faq.question: What if everyone tries to withdraw at once?
faq.answer: TLDR: Withdrawals would be delayed, but as long as there's no bad debt, everyone can withdraw eventually.  The protocol targets 80% pool utilization, which would mean 80% of funds are loaned out, and 20% are available for withdrawal. If utilization is too high, interest rates go up. This incentivizes borrowers to repay, and once they do, more people can withdraw.  You can read more about the relationship between utilization and interest rate in our docs.

faq.question: Will I earn a fixed interest rate, or does it change over time?
faq.answer: Interest rates change over time, based on supply and demand. The protocol controls this autonomously.

description: Morpho Blue is a noncustodial lending protocol implemented for the Ethereum Virtual Machine. It provides permissionless risk management and permissionless market creation with oracle agnostic pricing. It also enables higher collateralization factors, improved interest rates, and lower gas consumption. The protocol is designed to be a simple, immutable, and governance-minimized base layer that allows for a wide variety of other layers to be built on top. Morpho Blue also offers a convenient developer experience with a singleton implementation, callbacks, free flash loans, and account management features.
